posts.name: Josh Buker
posts.cooked:
After updating from 2020 to 2022, all of the code I’ve been using broke. I’ve pieced together the libraries and have started to find changes that happened in the code. I’ve been browsing through 2022 repositories to find differences, and the one im trying to get right now is compressors and double solenoids. Here is a link to my current build. https://github.com/metalmallards4692/frcRapidReact2022 and the errors I have are down below.  In there towards the very bottom it mentions a java runtime fatal error, so that is one of my larger concerns. If you have some updated references, and/or know what the runtime problem is. That would be greatly appreciated. Thank you.

in 2022 there is another Pneumatics module available, so when using the DoubleSolenoid constructor, you need to specify which Pneumatics module you’re using. For example: solenoid = new DoubleSolenoid(PneumaticsModuleType.CTREPCM, PORT_FORWARD, PORT_REVERSE); This seems to be the reason you’re code is crashing here, but there are other breaking changes in the 2022 update to look out for.

posts.name: Thad House
posts.cooked: That specific error code could correlate to a wiring issue as well. Ensure that your CAN bus is fully wired correctly.

posts.name: Josh Buker
posts.cooked: I found something similar when trying to get my build working, however it looks like you need to make a PCM object now, but in that constructor, where does it use the id of the   pcm. This is what I have If you have a link to how you setup the PCM and solenoids, that would be great, but in the meantime ill try to get into our shop and test out the new method.  Thank you.

posts.name: Thad House
posts.cooked: Your code looks fine. Its been modified correctly (Other then I would keep the default module number of 1 for other reasons). That error means there is a wiring issue, one thats causing the bus to error. You likely have a short somewhere on the bus. Either to ground, 5v or between the wires.

posts.name: Josh Buker
posts.cooked: Oh okay, ill make sure to look into that. Thank you.

posts.name: Josh Buker
posts.cooked: After working with our teacher, I realized that all of our new components are the Rev brand so my id work in phoenix tuner missed the majority of everything, so I downloaded the rev hardware software and need to go through that, so ill update whether or not that worked.
